# CSS Foundation System Rules

This project uses a strict CSS foundation system with specific constraints and patterns that must be followed.

## Core Constraint
**CRITICAL**: Only use CSS rules defined in [src/css/foundation/](mdc:src/css/foundation/) directory. Do not create, modify, or reference any CSS rules outside this directory unless explicitly instructed.

## Foundation Structure
The CSS foundation is organized into modular files:
- [src/css/foundation/foundation.css](mdc:src/css/foundation/foundation.css) - Main entry point that imports all modules
- [src/css/foundation/reset.css](mdc:src/css/foundation/reset.css) - Base reset styles
- [src/css/foundation/colors.css](mdc:src/css/foundation/colors.css) - Color system with primitives, scales, and semantic aliases
- [src/css/foundation/spacing.css](mdc:src/css/foundation/spacing.css) - Spacing variables and utilities
- [src/css/foundation/typography.css](mdc:src/css/foundation/typography.css) - Font system and text utilities
- [src/css/foundation/display.css](mdc:src/css/foundation/display.css) - Layout and display utilities
- [src/css/foundation/icons.css](mdc:src/css/foundation/icons.css) - Heroicon utility classes

## Code Organization Pattern
All CSS files use `/* #region {section name} */` and `/* #endregion */` comments to organize code sections.

## Main CSS Output
The compiled CSS is output to [src/css/swage.css](mdc:src/css/swage.css) which imports the foundation system.

## Variable Usage
- Use CSS custom properties (variables) defined in the foundation files
- Colors: `var(--color-*)` from [colors.css](mdc:src/css/foundation/colors.css)
- Spacing: `var(--spacing-*)` from [spacing.css](mdc:src/css/foundation/spacing.css)
- Typography: `var(--font-*)` and `var(--line-height-*)` from [typography.css](mdc:src/css/foundation/typography.css)

